**Note:** Save the following as `userdata.sh` in the same directory as your Terraform files:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "Hello from $(hostname -f)" > /var/www/html/index.html

# Register with target group
aws autoscaling detach-auto-scaling-instances --instance-ids $(curl -s http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/instance-id) --auto-scaling-group-names $(aws autoscaling describe-auto-scaling-groups --query 'AutoScalingGroups[0].AutoScalingGroupName' --output text) --no-should-decrement-desired-capacity
aws autoscaling attach-load-balancer-target-groups --auto-scaling-group-name $(aws autoscaling describe-auto-scaling-groups --query 'AutoScalingGroups[0].AutoScalingGroupName' --output text) --target-group-arns ${target_group_arn}
```

This configuration creates:
- VPC, subnets, and internet gateway
- Application Load Balancer (ALB) listening on port 80
- Target group for HTTP health checks
- Auto Scaling Group with 2 EC2 instances
- Security groups for ALB and EC2 instances
- User data script to install Apache and register instances with the target group

